        <p>
          QUANTA is a decentralized portfolio-based alpha signal generation network on Bittensor. Talented stock pickers exist globally—retail traders, quantitative researchers, AI/ML engineers—but they have no trustworthy way to prove skill or monetize it. Traditional trading competitions reward lucky gamblers who take maximum risk, and the equities market remains gatekept by hedge funds requiring credentials, connections, and capital.
        </p>
        <p>
          QUANTA runs a continuous, permissionless stock picking competition. Participants submit portfolio signals consisting of ticker-weight allocations, and validators score them using real market data and risk-adjusted metrics including Sortino, Calmar, and Sharpe ratios, max drawdown, and turnover penalties. Unlike competitions that reward raw returns, QUANTA rewards consistency and risk management across 7, 30, and 90-day rolling evaluation windows.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Signal Pool architecture overcomes Bittensor's 256 UID limitation, enabling unlimited participation. Signal generators stake proportional ante (skin-in-the-game), top performers win redistributed stake from underperformers, and a dual-revenue model (emissions + ante pool) keeps the long tail engaged while rewarding genuine alpha.
        </p>
        <p>
          QUANTA democratizes quantitative trading infrastructure. Anyone with stock picking skill—human or AI—can build a verifiable on-chain track record and earn crypto rewards.
        </p>
